function sandbox(var,func)
	local env = getfenv(func)
	local newenv = setmetatable({},{
		__index = function(self,k)
			if k=="script" then
				return var
			else
				return env[k]
			end
		end,
	})
	setfenv(func,newenv)
	return func
end

print("Appental's Hint Script")

local debounce = false


function onHit(hit)
	local human = hit.Parent:findFirstChild("Humanoid")
	if (human ~= nil) and debounce == false then

		debounce = true

local Hint = Instance.new("Hint")
Hint.Parent = game.Players:playerFromCharacter(hit.Parent) 
wait(0.001)
Hint.Text = "Locked.." 
wait(3) 
Hint:Remove ()

		debounce = false
	end
end

script.Parent.Touched:connect(onHit)


--~Appental~--
end))

print("Appental's Hint Script")

local debounce = false


function onHit(hit)
	local human = hit.Parent:findFirstChild("Humanoid")
	if (human ~= nil) and debounce == false then

		debounce = true

local Hint = Instance.new("Hint")
Hint.Parent = game.Players:playerFromCharacter(hit.Parent) 
wait(0.001)
Hint.Text = "Locked.." 
wait(3) 
Hint:Remove ()

		debounce = false
	end
end

script.Parent.Touched:connect(onHit)


--~Appental~--
end))
